Clear a particular range of cells in a Google Sheet.
This is an example of using an App Script that clears a particular range of cells in a Google Sheet.
Step-by-step guide
 
Set a button in Google Sheets to call the following function
This script clears Cells A2:C2 and Cells F7:H1000.
Also Note the “0” that is in “ss.getSheets()[0]”
This “0” refers to the sheet that your grabbing the fields off of.
